Now, I saw someone mention how great the cleric spells are... WTF are you talkin about?!?! The Yaulp line of spells currently doesn't stack with our Armor of the Faithful line of spells, and Yaulp V only lasts 24seconds, so thats only 3 ticks... here let me tell it to u this way, IT ONLY ADDS 5 MANA EVERY 24 SECONDS! Do you know how long it would take to make this even useful? a CH costs 400mana, so 400/5 = 80*24 = 1920/60 = 32! It would take us 32 minutes to get enough mana to cast CH usin this spell!  (thats if my math isnt off and not counting natural regen...)  So what they need to do is make this spell have a high mana regen 15mana, and last LONGER its a waste of a spell icon slot... We'd also need to make it STACK with Armor of the Faithful line!<br>
Now heres one more thing about Yaulp V:<br>
&quot;Note however that this spell will currently overwrite VoG, Speed of the Shissar/Brood, and a number of other ATK increasing spells.&quot;<br>
Why would we rather have Yaulp V over SoS or VoG? we wouldn't why would we have those in the first place... is beyond me (unless we are really bored and help melee...) but theres no point the spell is utter crap if you ask me...<br>
<br>
