<br>
I feel that these new spells will not effect a clerics role in the group, however in all fairness if the shaman and druid are getting a lesser version of our most widely used spell then we in turn should get a lesser version of theirs. I'd say a lesser form of the shaman slow or a weaker version of there pet would be nice, and it would help to make a cleric a more effective soloer, and the same goes for a lesser version of the druid snare. <br>
<br>
Another solution to equalizing clerics that has come to mind isn't new spells. VI should decrease the cast time on CH, and at the same time increase the clerics mana pool, or increase the clerics mana regen, although the increase in mana pool sounds better to me. When things get thick a lot of times the MA's life is dropping so fast that you don't have time to land a CH so you just chain cast devine light and hope the druid in the group can lend you a hand. Needless to say you also burn ALOT of mana doing this. Ok if VI doesn't agree with increasing clerics mana pool then maybe they should consider decreasing the mana usage on key spells, thats another idea.<br>
<br>
I don't think that swapping spells around is the solution, I think that increasing efficiency in cast time and mana usage will keep the clerics firmly rooted in there roll as MH. But once again my post and oppinion will hold no sway over VI.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah and someone mentioned pally rezes earlier, id just like to say that i love pally rezes, if im in a seb group and everyone lives but me, i dont need a cr i just need the pally rez, and yes this has happened to me before lol.<br>
<br>
Any way im sure your all sick of my rambling and this is why i tend to avoid posting, but id just like to ask each of you to realy consider the great benefit of the other classes having these spells, and think of all the things that you or your guilds could accomplish that you were once unable to do if your druids and shamans have this heal. Oh yeah and PL'ing will be a breeze to <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
